Sun 23 Apr 2017 07:42:20 PM EDT

On Kitt Peak National Observatory. It's in southern arizona (55 mi SW of
Tuscon). Established in 1958, under an NSF grant. Land is leased from Tohono
O'odham Nation.

Main instruments:
* Mayall 4m
* WIYN 3.5m
* 2.1, 1.3, 0.9, 0.4, reflectors.

Early claim to fame: hosting the first telescope (a 91cm reflector) used to
search for near-Earth asteroids, & calculating impact probability. 72% clear
nights.
